result.execSummary:
The defendant Chad Allen Pryatel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Chad Allen Pryatel is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Chad Allen Pryatel was found guilty of Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

AND PLEA AND SENTENCING 11:44 AM Defendant Chad Allen Pryatel in court, in custody.  Attorney Lance Morgan Nelsen in court for Chad Allen Pryatel.  Attorney Angela M Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney acknowledges receipt of the information, waives a formal reading. Defendant will enter plea to count 1. Sentence of 60 days jail with 0 days credit. Sentence will run consecutive to revocation in Douglas County file and to sentence in MN case file. $10 fine plus costs. 
Defendant pleads no contest to count 1. Attorney Nelsen stipulates to a factual basis. Court accepts the defendant's pleas and finds that the pleas have been knowingly and intelligently made. Defendant is found guilty. Count 2 is dismissed. 
Court orders in Count 1, a sentence of 60 days jail with 0 days credit. Sentence will run consecutive to revocation in Douglas County file 15CF217 and to sentence in MN case file. $10 fine plus costs. 120 days to pay.
